# Exclude generated release artifacts from `git archive` source exports.
# The release/ tree is npm-run-package output (checksums, manifest, deploy/
# source zips); it must never ship inside the source zip.
/release/ export-ignore
# Anchored, and docs/release/ explicitly re-included. The unanchored form also
# matched docs/release/, so RELEASE_ASSETS.md — documentation whose whole job is
# to tell a reviewer how to verify the release — was stripped from the very
# archive it ships in.
docs/release/** -export-ignore

# Exclude internal engineering docs (version-pinned plans, phase audits, PR
# writeups) from `git archive` source exports. They stay tracked for developers
# and history; they are not part of the public release artifact.
docs/_audit/ export-ignore
docs/architecture/v0.5.8-cleanup-plan.md export-ignore
docs/gate2-per-cloud-filter-plan.md export-ignore
docs/v0.5.7-plan.md export-ignore
docs/v0.5.7-object-e57-capture-lens.md export-ignore

# Exclude release-process deliberation from `git archive` source exports.
#
# READINESS_REPORT_* is the go/no-go record for a cut: open blockers, what is
# not ready, what must happen before tagging. That is internal reasoning about
# whether to ship, not documentation of what shipped, and nothing public links
# to it. The public honesty surface is KNOWN_LIMITATIONS + VALIDATION_REPORT,
# which state what the release does and does not establish.
READINESS_REPORT_*.md export-ignore

# Superseded per-release evidence. The archive should carry the reports for the
# version it IS, not a pile of prior ones a reader has to date-sort. Kept in
# the repository and in history.
#
# NOT excluded: VALIDATION_REPORT_v0.5.9.md, which this release inherits its
# terrain/measurement claims from and which README, ARTIFACT_EVALUATION and
# AI_ASSISTANCE all link to. It is load-bearing evidence, not clutter.
VALIDATION_REPORT_v0.6.0-alpha.1.md export-ignore
REPRODUCIBILITY_v0.6.0-alpha.1.md export-ignore
# The scholarly archive carries exactly one truth-document set — the shipped
# version's. Every prerelease notes/limitations/reproducibility/validation
# file stays in git history and on GitHub, but out of the deposit, so a
# researcher is never unsure which evidence applies to v0.6.0 (and the alpha.2
# validation report's link into docs/_audit/, itself export-ignored, cannot
# dangle in the archive).
RELEASE_NOTES_v0.6.0-alpha.*.md export-ignore
KNOWN_LIMITATIONS_v0.6.0-alpha.*.md export-ignore
REPRODUCIBILITY_v0.6.0-alpha.*.md export-ignore
VALIDATION_REPORT_v0.6.0-alpha.*.md export-ignore

# Release planning: goals, baselines and sequencing for a cut. Same class as
# a readiness report - what we intend to do and why, not what the release is.
docs/architecture/stabilization-release-plan.md export-ignore
